# Learn-I3-Window-Manager
I3 is a pretty easy to use window manager, what makes it tricky is that people put in settings without a full understanding of their actoins

I'm here to make i3 the easy to use Window Manager, make it faster for you, and in the end to give you a better computing experiance.

So first of all you will have to download i3
For you ubuntu based users that will be:
sudo apt-get install i3 -y

After you have that done open up a new X session by hitting CTRL+ALT+F1 (to get back to your old one hit CTRL+ALT+F7)
From here you need to login
once you're logged in, type in:
startx i3

This will start up i3, you're not using i3.
